race.comment: MCKEON (6) flew the lids with a sensational early split and led throughout to score an impressive win by 10 lengths over 484m at this track (27.31). Won at her only start from this draw. Form reads well for this. WESTERN LIES (2) is a well performed dog and winner of 14 races who is worth forgiving after finishing out of the placings at this track (28.10). Has a good record here at this journey. Cannot be left out. DASHING DENNIS (1) produced a modest effort most recently when sixth at Grafton over 450m behind I'm What's Next (25.92) in a Grade 4/5. One of the main contenders. GIVE ME BUCKS (3) was in the money last time at Q Lakeside (25.42) in a Grade 5, finishing a 3 length second. Has already won three times from this draw.
